          <p><strong><a href="/library/natural-procreative-technology-naprotechnology-for-infertility-take-home-baby-ra-recv02qu0r8ycnzoa/">Sanchez-Mendez et al. (2025)</a></strong> published the largest NaProTechnology cohort study to date in <em>Frontiers in Reproductive Health</em>. The study followed 1,310 couples and reported a crude live birth rate of 35.3%. Using Kaplan-Meier survival analysis, the adjusted cumulative live birth rate reached 50.0% at 24 months and 62.1% at full follow-up (36+ months). This is the most methodologically detailed RRM outcomes study published to date.<sup><a href="#ref-25" id="cite-25c">25</a></sup> The study applied the NaProTechnology protocol at Fertilitas Center in Madrid, Spain: the same clinical framework used in Creighton/NaPro practice worldwide, implemented by a clinical group independent of Boyle's Dublin cohort.</p>

